      <h2>Best Fuel Credit Cards in India</h2>
      <p>For daily commuters and frequent drivers, fuel is one of the biggest recurring expenses. Every time you pay at a petrol pump using a regular credit card, the payment gateway charges a 1% fuel surcharge (plus GST) — adding ₹10-₹15 per ₹1,000 of fuel purchased. Fuel credit cards waive this surcharge entirely and many also offer additional cashback or reward points on fuel transactions, effectively saving you 2-5% on every fill-up.</p>
      <p>The best fuel cards are co-branded with Indian oil companies like IOCL, BPCL, or HPCL, offering exclusive savings at specific networks. General fuel cards from banks like HDFC, ICICI, and Axis offer surcharge waivers across all petrol pumps nationwide.</p>

      <h2>Key Features of Fuel Credit Cards</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Fuel Surcharge Waiver:</strong> Complete 1% surcharge waiver on fuel purchases between ₹400-₹5,000 per transaction</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Accelerated Fuel Rewards:</strong> Earn 2X-5X reward points or up to 5% cashback specifically on fuel station transactions</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>All-Pump Acceptance:</strong> General fuel cards work at all IOCL, BPCL, and HPCL petrol pumps across India</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Co-Branded Benefits:</strong> IOCL/BPCL co-branded cards offer additional loyalty points redeemable for free fuel</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Auto-Assist Benefits:</strong> Some cards include roadside assistance, towing services, and flat tyre repair</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Non-Fuel Rewards:</strong> Fuel cards also earn rewards on groceries, dining, and other everyday spends</li>
      </ul>

