      <h2>Eligibility for Fuel Credit Cards</h2>
      <p>Fuel credit cards are accessible to most working professionals. Here are the typical requirements:</p>

      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years for salaried; 21-65 years for self-employed and business owners</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹15,000-₹25,000/month for co-branded fuel cards; ₹25,000+ for premium fuel cards</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> 680+ CIBIL for basic fuel cards; 720+ for cards with higher rewards and limits</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Vehicle Ownership:</strong> Not mandatory but helps demonstrate fuel spending pattern to the bank</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Salaried, self-employed, professionals, or business owners with verifiable income</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar, income proof, bank statements, and photograph</li>
      </ul>

