  <section class="faq-section"><div class="container">
    <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p>Common questions about fuel credit cards and fuel surcharge waiver</p></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">What is fuel surcharge and how is it waived?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Fuel surcharge is a 1% fee (plus 18% GST, totalling ~1.18%) charged by payment gateways when you use a credit card at petrol pumps. On a ₹5,000 fuel purchase, this adds ~₹59 in surcharge. Fuel credit cards waive this surcharge — the bank absorbs the cost as a card benefit. Most cards waive surcharge on transactions between ₹400 and ₹5,000, with a monthly cap of ₹100-₹250 on the waiver. This means if you spend ₹10,000 monthly on fuel, you save ₹1,200-₹1,400 per year just from the surcharge waiver alone.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Should I get a co-branded or general fuel card?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Choose a co-branded card (HDFC IndianOil, ICICI HPCL, SBI BPCL) if 80%+ of your fuel purchases are from a specific oil company's stations — you'll earn 4-5% savings vs. 1-2% from general cards. Choose a general fuel card (like Axis ACE or HDFC MoneyBack+) if you fill up at whichever pump is convenient — you'll get surcharge waiver at all pumps with consistent savings. If your city has a mix of stations and you don't have a strong preference, a general card is more practical and flexible.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Is there a minimum and maximum transaction amount for fuel surcharge waiver?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, most fuel credit cards waive surcharge only on transactions between ₹400 and ₹5,000 per swipe. Transactions below ₹400 or above ₹5,000 don't qualify for the waiver. To maximise savings on large fuel purchases, split them into multiple transactions of ₹4,000-₹5,000 each. The monthly surcharge waiver is also typically capped at ₹100-₹250 depending on the card. Always check your specific card's terms for exact limits.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">How much can I save with a fuel credit card per year?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Annual savings depend on your fuel spending and card type. For a monthly fuel spend of ₹8,000: (1) Surcharge waiver alone saves ~₹1,130/year, (2) A co-branded card at 5% cashback on fuel adds ~₹4,800/year, (3) Total savings: ~₹5,930/year. Even with a basic general card offering only surcharge waiver and 1% fuel rewards, you'd save ~₹2,000-₹2,500/year. For high-spending commuters filling ₹15,000+/month in fuel, a co-branded fuel card can deliver savings of ₹8,000-₹10,000 annually — far exceeding the card's annual fee.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Do fuel cards also offer rewards on non-fuel purchases?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, most fuel credit cards earn rewards on non-fuel spending too, though at lower rates. For example, SBI BPCL gives 13X rewards at BPCL stations but also earns 1X on all other spends. ICICI HPCL Super Save offers 5% on HPCL fuel and 2X on groceries and dining. General cards like Axis ACE offer 2% flat cashback on all spends plus fuel surcharge waiver. If your non-fuel spending is significant, consider a card that balances good fuel benefits with decent general earning rates.</div></div></div>
    </div>
